          <!--WHAT IS PH-->
          <table>
            <tr>
              <td>
                <img style="width: 150px; max-height: 1000px" src="Graphics/sensor/pH .png" alt="pH symbol">
              </td>
              <td>
                <h2 style="color: #12DF89; border-bottom: 2px solid #12DF89;"">
                  What is pH?
                </h2>
                <p class="main-text">
                  pH is the measure of how acidic or basic a substance is. 
                  It ranges from 0 to 14, with 0 being extremely acidic, 14 being highly basic, 
                  and 7 being neutral. 
                </p>
                <p class="main-text">
                  The ideal pH for drinking water is generally around 7,
                  which is considered neutral. Water that is too acidic or too basic 
                  can affect its taste, safety, and its ability to interact with 
                  substances in our bodies, resulting in unsafe drinking water.
                </p>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </table>

